    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      double getMasterOutputCurrent()
      Gets the output current of the master of the gearbox, in amps
      double getMasterVbus()
      Gets the current battery voltage ("vbus") in volts, as read by the master
      double getOutputPercent()
      Gets the current "percent vbus" output of the motor controller. In other words, the percentage of the battery voltage that is being applied to the motor. -1.0 < x < 1.0
      double getOutputVoltage()
      Gets the output voltage of the gearbox, in volts
      void link()
      Links the slaves to the master. This is called automatically when the gearbox is created, but can be called from user code if, for example, a motor controller resets and the gearbox needs to be reinitialized
      void set(ISmartGearbox.CommonControlMode controlMode, double setpoint)
      Sets the setpoint of the gearbox with the given control mode.
      void set(ISmartGearbox.CommonControlMode controlMode, double setpoint, double arbFF)
      Sets the setpoint of the gearbox with the given control mode and arbitrary feed forward.
      boolean setDeadband(double deadbandPercent)
      Sets the neutral deadband, or in other words the percentage on either side of zero to ignore. Note that this implementation will configure the deadband for both open and closed loop control modes.
      boolean setNeutralMode(ISmartGearbox.CommonNeutralMode mode)
      Sets the neutral mode of the gearbox. This configures the setting on ALL attached motor controllers
      boolean setPIDF(double kP, double kI, double kD, double kF, int slot)
      Configures the PIDF gains into the specified slot
      boolean setPIDF(PIDFTemplate template, int slot)
      Configures the PIDF template into the specified slot
      boolean setRampRate(double secondsFromNeutralToFull)
      Sets the ramp rate of the gearbox. The ramp rate is the number of seconds it should take to go from 0.0 to 1.0 output given an instantaneous change in setpoint. Essentially smooths out the output of the motor. Note that this configures the ramp rate for both open and closed loop control modes.

Essentially smooths out the output of the motor. Note that this configures the ramp rate for both open and closed loop control modes.

      • set

        void set(ISmartGearbox.CommonControlMode controlMode,
         double setpoint)

        Sets the setpoint of the gearbox with the given control mode.

        In position mode, the setpoint should be in radians (as measured by the sensor) In velocity mode, the setpoint should be in radians per second (as measured by the sensor)

      • set

        void set(ISmartGearbox.CommonControlMode controlMode,
         double setpoint,
         double arbFF)

        Sets the setpoint of the gearbox with the given control mode and arbitrary feed forward.

        The arbitrary feed forward should be in volts, with a maximum value of 12.0

        In position mode, the setpoint should be in radians (as measured by the sensor) In velocity mode, the setpoint should be in radians per second (as measured by the sensor)
